		<div id="comment_body_64249198">Due to their dominance in search, Microsoft and Google hold all the power here. They can technically honor a "Do Not Train AI" flag for sites that set it in robots.txt.<nobr> <wbr></nobr>...but they can also then stop indexing those sites for general search (because technically their ranking algorithms also employ some level of "AI"). Those sites will be essentially forced to allow AI training if they don't want their traffic to dry up. At the end of the day, Medium, NYT, et al need Google and Bing more than the other way ar</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64249198">

</div>
